      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was completed and grid convergence index values were computed. The hemolysis scalar showed acceptable convergence behavior consistent with engineering practice for rotating machinery, and the velocity field GCI was below 5%. Given the overall robustness of the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification framework applied downstream, the team considered discretization uncertainty to be adequately bounded for decision-making purposes. Minor residual oscillations in the hemolysis GCI at peak-speed conditions were noted as within expected variability for complex rotating flow."
